{"id":"1805.05162","submitter":"Liangliang Shi","authors":"L. Shi, N. Baboi and R.M. Jones","title":"Beam Phase Retrieval based on Higher Order Modes in Cylindrical SRF\n  Cavities","comments":"16 pages, 14 figures, submitted to Review of Scientific Instruments","journal-ref":null,"doi":"10.1063/1.5040191","report-no":"DESY 18-073","categories":"physics.acc-ph","license":"http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/4.0/","abstract":"  The control of beam phase relative to the accelerating RF field within a\nsuperconducting cavity is important in many accelerator applications and is of\nparticular importance for a free electron laser facility. As standard practice,\nthe phase is usually inferred from the beam-induced transient field with\nrespect to a timing reference. We report here on an alternative and novel means\nof beam phase determination based on beam-excited higher order electromagnetic\nmodes and the accelerating electromagnetic mode, which are conveniently\navailable from the same coupler. The monopole modes are immune to the electron\nbeam offset and therefore are best suited for the task. A coupled circuit model\nis used to assist the development and to rapidly assess the facility of the\nmethod. Simulations based on the circuit model indicate that the resolution of\nthis system depends critically on the signal to noise ratio. Beam-based\nmeasurements with a test setup were carried out at the European XFEL, Germany.\nBased on this new method we have routinely obtained a resolution of 0.1{\\deg}.\nThe best resolution observed with the current setup was 0.03{\\deg}. These\nresults agree very well with the predictions from those predicted by a circuit\nmodel. The system investigated here can be used to provide diagnostic\ninformation for the current LLRF system employed in the European XFEL. To this\nend, the associated electronics are under development. This monitor is the\nfirst of its kind that can deliver direct and online measurements of the beam\nphase with respect to the RF field.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 14 May 2018 13:24:22 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-11-14"}
